Quote:  (2.) Batten and wire fence, at least 3 ft. 9 in. high, of substantial material, firmly erected, with one or more wires, not lighter than No. 8 in steel, or black or galvanised iron; battens either driven securely into the ground and securely stapled, or intertwined in wires in an upright position, and not more than 3 in. apart.
Notes:  1895 Fencing Act in 1902 Settler's Handbook of NZ 161


